4 Days Ago Francis Enobore, the spokesperson for the correctional centre said the gunmen used explosives to blast their way through the centre’s administrative block before accessing the entrance into the prisons yard. “Six inmates have so far voluntarily returned to the facility while 35 inmates refused to escape from custody during the attack,” Mr Enobore had said in a statement, shortly after the incident. Several states in Nigeria are contending with various security challenges, including kidnapping for ransom, communal conflicts, and frequent clashes between herders and farmers.